{"word":"αὐαίνω","slug":"αὐαίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αὐαίνω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>αὔω</el> <i>to dry</i>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to dry</i> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to dry</i> or <i>parch up</i>, <el>αὐανῶ βίον</el> <i>I shall waste</i> life <i>away</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>αὐανθείς</el> <i>withered</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a>, <el>αὐανοῦμαι</el> <i>I shall wither away</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}